  16 r"""Navidation Environment. Includes the following classes along with some
  17 helper functions.
  18   Building: Loads buildings, computes traversibility, exposes functionality for
  19     rendering images.
  20   
  21   GridWorld: Base class which implements functionality for moving an agent on a
  22     grid world.
  23   
  24   NavigationEnv: Base class which generates navigation problems on a grid world.
  25   
  26   VisualNavigationEnv: Builds upon NavigationEnv and Building to provide
  27     interface that is used externally to train the agent. 
  28   
  29   MeshMapper: Class used for distilling the model, testing the mapper.
  30   
  31   BuildingMultiplexer: Wrapper class that instantiates a VisualNavigationEnv for
  32     each building and multiplexes between them as needed.
  33 """

  79 def _get_semantic_maps(folder_name, building_name, map, flip):
  80   # Load file from the cache.
  81   file_name = '{:s}_{:d}_{:d}_{:d}_{:d}_{:d}_{:d}.pkl'
  82   file_name = file_name.format(building_name, map.size[0], map.size[1],
  83                                map.origin[0], map.origin[1], map.resolution,
  84                                flip)
  85   file_name = os.path.join(folder_name, file_name)
  86   logging.info('Loading semantic maps from %s.', file_name)
  87 
  88   if fu.exists(file_name):
  89     a = utils.load_variables(file_name)
  90     maps = a['maps'] #HxWx#C
  91     cats = a['cats']
  92   else:
  93     logging.error('file_name: %s not found.', file_name)
  94     maps = None
  95     cats = None
  96   return maps, cats

  98 def _select_classes(all_maps, all_cats, cats_to_use):
  99   inds = []
 100   for c in cats_to_use:
 101     ind = all_cats.index(c)
 102     inds.append(ind)
 103   out_maps = all_maps[:,:,inds]
 104   return out_maps

 106 def _get_room_dimensions(file_name, resolution, origin, flip=False):
 107   if fu.exists(file_name):
 108     a = utils.load_variables(file_name)['room_dimension']
 109     names = a.keys()
 110     dims = np.concatenate(a.values(), axis=0).reshape((-1,6))
 111     ind = np.argsort(names)
 112     dims = dims[ind,:]
 113     names = [names[x] for x in ind]
 114     if flip:
 115       dims_new = dims*1
 116       dims_new[:,1] = -dims[:,4]
 117       dims_new[:,4] = -dims[:,1]
 118       dims = dims_new*1
 119 
 120     dims = dims*100.
 121     dims[:,0] = dims[:,0] - origin[0]
 122     dims[:,1] = dims[:,1] - origin[1]
 123     dims[:,3] = dims[:,3] - origin[0]
 124     dims[:,4] = dims[:,4] - origin[1]
 125     dims = dims / resolution
 126     out = {'names': names, 'dims': dims}
 127   else:
 128     out = None
 129   return out
 130 
 131 def _filter_rooms(room_dims, room_regex):
 132   pattern = re.compile(room_regex)
 133   ind = []
 134   for i, name in enumerate(room_dims['names']):
 135     if pattern.match(name):
 136       ind.append(i)
 137   new_room_dims = {}
 138   new_room_dims['names'] = [room_dims['names'][i] for i in ind]
 139   new_room_dims['dims'] = room_dims['dims'][ind,:]*1
 140   return new_room_dims
 141 
 142 def _label_nodes_with_room_id(xyt, room_dims):
 143   # Label the room with the ID into things.
 144   node_room_id = -1*np.ones((xyt.shape[0], 1))
 145   dims = room_dims['dims']
 146   for x, name in enumerate(room_dims['names']):
 147     all_ = np.concatenate((xyt[:,[0]] >= dims[x,0],
 148                            xyt[:,[0]] <= dims[x,3],
 149                            xyt[:,[1]] >= dims[x,1],
 150                            xyt[:,[1]] <= dims[x,4]), axis=1)
 151     node_room_id[np.all(all_, axis=1), 0] = x
 152   return node_room_id
 153 
 154 def get_path_ids(start_node_id, end_node_id, pred_map):
 155   id = start_node_id
 156   path = [id]
 157   while id != end_node_id:
 158     id = pred_map[id]
 159     path.append(id)
 160   return path

 162 def image_pre(images, modalities):
 163   # Assumes images are ...xHxWxC.
 164   # We always assume images are RGB followed by Depth.
 165   if 'depth' in modalities:
 166     d = images[...,-1][...,np.newaxis]*1.
 167     d[d < 0.01] = np.NaN; isnan = np.isnan(d);
 168     d = 100./d; d[isnan] = 0.;
 169     images = np.concatenate((images[...,:-1], d, isnan), axis=images.ndim-1)
 170   if 'rgb' in modalities:
 171     images[...,:3] = images[...,:3]*1. - 128
 172   return images

 174 def _get_relative_goal_loc(goal_loc, loc, theta):
 175   r = np.sqrt(np.sum(np.square(goal_loc - loc), axis=1))
 176   t = np.arctan2(goal_loc[:,1] - loc[:,1], goal_loc[:,0] - loc[:,0])
 177   t = t-theta[:,0] + np.pi/2
 178   return np.expand_dims(r,axis=1), np.expand_dims(t, axis=1)
 179 
 180 def _gen_perturbs(rng, batch_size, num_steps, lr_flip, delta_angle, delta_xy,
 181                   structured):
 182   perturbs = []
 183   for i in range(batch_size):
 184     # Doing things one by one for each episode in this batch. This way this
 185     # remains replicatable even when we change the batch size.
 186     p = np.zeros((num_steps+1, 4))
 187     if lr_flip:
 188       # Flip the whole trajectory.
 189       p[:,3] = rng.rand(1)-0.5
 190     if delta_angle > 0:
 191       if structured:
 192         p[:,2] = (rng.rand(1)-0.5)* delta_angle
 193       else:
 194         p[:,2] = (rng.rand(p.shape[0])-0.5)* delta_angle
 195     if delta_xy > 0:
 196       if structured:
 197         p[:,:2] = (rng.rand(1, 2)-0.5)*delta_xy
 198       else:
 199         p[:,:2] = (rng.rand(p.shape[0], 2)-0.5)*delta_xy
 200     perturbs.append(p)
 201   return perturbs

 209 class GridWorld():
 210   def __init__(self):
 211     """Class members that will be assigned by any class that actually uses this
 212     class."""
 213     self.restrict_to_largest_cc = None
 214     self.robot = None
 215     self.env = None
 216     self.category_list = None
 217     self.traversible = None
 218 
 219   def get_loc_axis(self, node, delta_theta, perturb=None):
 220     """Based on the node orientation returns X, and Y axis. Used to sample the
 221     map in egocentric coordinate frame.
 222     """
 223     if type(node) == tuple:
 224       node = np.array([node])
 225     if perturb is None:
 226       perturb = np.zeros((node.shape[0], 4))
 227     xyt = self.to_actual_xyt_vec(node)
 228     x = xyt[:,[0]] + perturb[:,[0]]
 229     y = xyt[:,[1]] + perturb[:,[1]]
 230     t = xyt[:,[2]] + perturb[:,[2]]
 231     theta = t*delta_theta
 232     loc = np.concatenate((x,y), axis=1)
 233     x_axis = np.concatenate((np.cos(theta), np.sin(theta)), axis=1)
 234     y_axis = np.concatenate((np.cos(theta+np.pi/2.), np.sin(theta+np.pi/2.)),
 235                             axis=1)
 236     # Flip the sampled map where need be.
 237     y_axis[np.where(perturb[:,3] > 0)[0], :] *= -1.
 238     return loc, x_axis, y_axis, theta
 239 
 240   def to_actual_xyt(self, pqr):
 241     """Converts from node to location on the map."""
 242     (p, q, r) = pqr
 243     if self.task.n_ori == 6:
 244       out = (p - q * 0.5 + self.task.origin_loc[0],
 245              q * np.sqrt(3.) / 2. + self.task.origin_loc[1], r)
 246     elif self.task.n_ori == 4:
 247       out = (p + self.task.origin_loc[0],
 248              q + self.task.origin_loc[1], r)
 249     return out
 250 
 251   def to_actual_xyt_vec(self, pqr):
 252     """Converts from node array to location array on the map."""
 253     p = pqr[:,0][:, np.newaxis]
 254     q = pqr[:,1][:, np.newaxis]
 255     r = pqr[:,2][:, np.newaxis]
 256     if self.task.n_ori == 6:
 257       out = np.concatenate((p - q * 0.5 + self.task.origin_loc[0],
 258                             q * np.sqrt(3.) / 2. + self.task.origin_loc[1],
 259                             r), axis=1)
 260     elif self.task.n_ori == 4:
 261       out = np.concatenate((p + self.task.origin_loc[0],
 262                             q + self.task.origin_loc[1],
 263                             r), axis=1)
 264     return out
 265 
 266   def raw_valid_fn_vec(self, xyt):
 267     """Returns if the given set of nodes is valid or not."""
 268     height = self.traversible.shape[0]
 269     width = self.traversible.shape[1]
 270     x = np.round(xyt[:,[0]]).astype(np.int32)
 271     y = np.round(xyt[:,[1]]).astype(np.int32)
 272     is_inside = np.all(np.concatenate((x >= 0, y >= 0,
 273                                        x < width, y < height), axis=1), axis=1)
 274     x = np.minimum(np.maximum(x, 0), width-1)
 275     y = np.minimum(np.maximum(y, 0), height-1)
 276     ind = np.ravel_multi_index((y,x), self.traversible.shape)
 277     is_traversible = self.traversible.ravel()[ind]
 278 
 279     is_valid = np.all(np.concatenate((is_inside[:,np.newaxis], is_traversible),
 280                                      axis=1), axis=1)
 281     return is_valid
 282 
 283 
 284   def valid_fn_vec(self, pqr):
 285     """Returns if the given set of nodes is valid or not."""
 286     xyt = self.to_actual_xyt_vec(np.array(pqr))
 287     height = self.traversible.shape[0]
 288     width = self.traversible.shape[1]
 289     x = np.round(xyt[:,[0]]).astype(np.int32)
 290     y = np.round(xyt[:,[1]]).astype(np.int32)
 291     is_inside = np.all(np.concatenate((x >= 0, y >= 0,
 292                                        x < width, y < height), axis=1), axis=1)
 293     x = np.minimum(np.maximum(x, 0), width-1)
 294     y = np.minimum(np.maximum(y, 0), height-1)
 295     ind = np.ravel_multi_index((y,x), self.traversible.shape)
 296     is_traversible = self.traversible.ravel()[ind]
 297 
 298     is_valid = np.all(np.concatenate((is_inside[:,np.newaxis], is_traversible),
 299                                      axis=1), axis=1)
 300     return is_valid
 301 
 302   def get_feasible_actions(self, node_ids):
 303     """Returns the feasible set of actions from the current node."""
 304     a = np.zeros((len(node_ids), self.task_params.num_actions), dtype=np.int32)
 305     gtG = self.task.gtG
 306     next_node = []
 307     for i, c in enumerate(node_ids):
 308       neigh = gtG.vertex(c).out_neighbours()
 309       neigh_edge = gtG.vertex(c).out_edges()
 310       nn = {}
 311       for n, e in zip(neigh, neigh_edge):
 312         _ = gtG.ep['action'][e]
 313         a[i,_] = 1
 314         nn[_] = int(n)
 315       next_node.append(nn)
 316     return a, next_node
 317 
 318   def take_action(self, current_node_ids, action):
 319     """Returns the new node after taking the action action. Stays at the current
 320     node if the action is invalid."""
 321     actions, next_node_ids = self.get_feasible_actions(current_node_ids)
 322     new_node_ids = []
 323     for i, (c,a) in enumerate(zip(current_node_ids, action)):
 324       if actions[i,a] == 1:
 325         new_node_ids.append(next_node_ids[i][a])
 326       else:
 327         new_node_ids.append(c)
 328     return new_node_ids
 329 
 330   def set_r_obj(self, r_obj):
 331     """Sets the SwiftshaderRenderer object used for rendering."""
 332     self.r_obj = r_obj

 334 class Building(GridWorld):
 335   def __init__(self, building_name, robot, env,
 336                category_list=None, small=False, flip=False, logdir=None,
 337                building_loader=None):
 338 
 339     self.restrict_to_largest_cc = True
 340     self.robot = robot
 341     self.env = env
 342     self.logdir = logdir
 343 
 344     # Load the building meta data.
 345     building = building_loader.load_building(building_name)
 346     if small:
 347       building['mesh_names'] = building['mesh_names'][:5]
 348 
 349     # New code.
 350     shapess = building_loader.load_building_meshes(building)
 351     if flip:
 352       for shapes in shapess:
 353         shapes.flip_shape()
 354 
 355     vs = []
 356     for shapes in shapess:
 357       vs.append(shapes.get_vertices()[0])
 358     vs = np.concatenate(vs, axis=0)
 359     map = make_map(env.padding, env.resolution, vertex=vs, sc=100.)
 360     map = compute_traversibility(
 361         map, robot.base, robot.height, robot.radius, env.valid_min,
 362         env.valid_max, env.num_point_threshold, shapess=shapess, sc=100.,
 363         n_samples_per_face=env.n_samples_per_face)
 364 
 365     room_dims = _get_room_dimensions(building['room_dimension_file'],
 366                                      env.resolution, map.origin, flip=flip)
 367     class_maps, class_map_names = _get_semantic_maps(
 368         building['class_map_folder'], building_name, map, flip)
 369 
 370     self.class_maps      = class_maps
 371     self.class_map_names = class_map_names
 372     self.building        = building
 373     self.shapess         = shapess
 374     self.map             = map
 375     self.traversible     = map.traversible*1
 376     self.building_name   = building_name
 377     self.room_dims       = room_dims
 378     self.flipped         = flip
 379     self.renderer_entitiy_ids = []
 380 
 381     if self.restrict_to_largest_cc:
 382       self.traversible = pick_largest_cc(self.traversible)
 383 
 384   def load_building_into_scene(self):
 385     # Loads the scene.
 386     self.renderer_entitiy_ids += self.r_obj.load_shapes(self.shapess)
 387     # Free up memory, we dont need the mesh or the materials anymore.
 388     self.shapess = None
 389 
 390   def add_entity_at_nodes(self, nodes, height, shape):
 391     xyt = self.to_actual_xyt_vec(nodes)
 392     nxy = xyt[:,:2]*1.
 393     nxy = nxy * self.map.resolution
 394     nxy = nxy + self.map.origin
 395     Ts = np.concatenate((nxy, nxy[:,:1]), axis=1)
 396     Ts[:,2] = height; Ts = Ts / 100.;
 397 
 398     # Merge all the shapes into a single shape and add that shape.
 399     shape.replicate_shape(Ts)
 400     entity_ids = self.r_obj.load_shapes([shape])
 401     self.renderer_entitiy_ids += entity_ids
 402     return entity_ids
 403 
 404   def add_shapes(self, shapes):
 405     scene = self.r_obj.viz.scene()
 406     for shape in shapes:
 407       scene.AddShape(shape)
 408 
 409   def add_materials(self, materials):
 410     scene = self.r_obj.viz.scene()
 411     for material in materials:
 412       scene.AddOrUpdateMaterial(material)
 413 
 414   def set_building_visibility(self, visibility):
 415     self.r_obj.set_entity_visible(self.renderer_entitiy_ids, visibility)
 416 
 417   def render_nodes(self, nodes, perturb=None, aux_delta_theta=0.):
 418     self.set_building_visibility(True)
 419     if perturb is None:
 420       perturb = np.zeros((len(nodes), 4))
 421 
 422     imgs = []
 423     r = 2
 424     elevation_z = r * np.tan(np.deg2rad(self.robot.camera_elevation_degree))
 425 
 426     for i in range(len(nodes)):
 427       xyt = self.to_actual_xyt(nodes[i])
 428       lookat_theta = 3.0 * np.pi / 2.0 - (xyt[2]+perturb[i,2]+aux_delta_theta) * (self.task.delta_theta)
 429       nxy = np.array([xyt[0]+perturb[i,0], xyt[1]+perturb[i,1]]).reshape(1, -1)
 430       nxy = nxy * self.map.resolution
 431       nxy = nxy + self.map.origin
 432       camera_xyz = np.zeros((1, 3))
 433       camera_xyz[...] = [nxy[0, 0], nxy[0, 1], self.robot.sensor_height]
 434       camera_xyz = camera_xyz / 100.
 435       lookat_xyz = np.array([-r * np.sin(lookat_theta),
 436                              -r * np.cos(lookat_theta), elevation_z])
 437       lookat_xyz = lookat_xyz + camera_xyz[0, :]
 438       self.r_obj.position_camera(camera_xyz[0, :].tolist(),
 439                                  lookat_xyz.tolist(), [0.0, 0.0, 1.0])
 440       img = self.r_obj.render(take_screenshot=True, output_type=0)
 441       img = [x for x in img if x is not None]
 442       img = np.concatenate(img, axis=2).astype(np.float32)
 443       if perturb[i,3]>0:
 444         img = img[:,::-1,:]
 445       imgs.append(img)
 446 
 447     self.set_building_visibility(False)
 448     return imgs

 451 class MeshMapper(Building):
 452   def __init__(self, robot, env, task_params, building_name, category_list,
 453                flip, logdir=None, building_loader=None):
 454     Building.__init__(self, building_name, robot, env, category_list,
 455                       small=task_params.toy_problem, flip=flip, logdir=logdir,
 456                       building_loader=building_loader)
 457     self.task_params = task_params
 458     self.task = None
 459     self._preprocess_for_task(self.task_params.building_seed)
 460 
 461   def _preprocess_for_task(self, seed):
 462     if self.task is None or self.task.seed != seed:
 463       rng = np.random.RandomState(seed)
 464       origin_loc = get_graph_origin_loc(rng, self.traversible)
 465       self.task = utils.Foo(seed=seed, origin_loc=origin_loc,
 466                             n_ori=self.task_params.n_ori)
 467       G = generate_graph(self.valid_fn_vec,
 468                                   self.task_params.step_size, self.task.n_ori,
 469                                   (0, 0, 0))
 470       gtG, nodes, nodes_to_id = convert_to_graph_tool(G)
 471       self.task.gtG = gtG
 472       self.task.nodes = nodes
 473       self.task.delta_theta = 2.0*np.pi/(self.task.n_ori*1.)
 474       self.task.nodes_to_id = nodes_to_id
 475       logging.info('Building %s, #V=%d, #E=%d', self.building_name,
 476                    self.task.nodes.shape[0], self.task.gtG.num_edges())
 477 
 478       if self.logdir is not None:
 479         write_traversible = cv2.applyColorMap(self.traversible.astype(np.uint8)*255, cv2.COLORMAP_JET)
 480         img_path = os.path.join(self.logdir,
 481                                 '{:s}_{:d}_graph.png'.format(self.building_name,
 482                                                              seed))
 483         node_xyt = self.to_actual_xyt_vec(self.task.nodes)
 484         plt.set_cmap('jet');
 485         fig, ax = utils.subplot(plt, (1,1), (12,12))
 486         ax.plot(node_xyt[:,0], node_xyt[:,1], 'm.')
 487         ax.imshow(self.traversible, origin='lower');
 488         ax.set_axis_off(); ax.axis('equal');
 489         ax.set_title('{:s}, {:d}, {:d}'.format(self.building_name,
 490                                                self.task.nodes.shape[0],
 491                                                self.task.gtG.num_edges()))
 492         if self.room_dims is not None:
 493           for i, r in enumerate(self.room_dims['dims']*1):
 494             min_ = r[:3]*1
 495             max_ = r[3:]*1
 496             xmin, ymin, zmin = min_
 497             xmax, ymax, zmax = max_
 498 
 499             ax.plot([xmin, xmax, xmax, xmin, xmin],
 500                     [ymin, ymin, ymax, ymax, ymin], 'g')
 501         with fu.fopen(img_path, 'w') as f:
 502           fig.savefig(f, bbox_inches='tight', transparent=True, pad_inches=0)
 503         plt.close(fig)

 506   def _gen_rng(self, rng):
 507     # instances is a list of list of node_ids.
 508     if self.task_params.move_type == 'circle':
 509       _, _, _, _, paths = rng_target_dist_field(self.task_params.batch_size,
 510                                                 self.task.gtG, rng, 0, 1,
 511                                                 compute_path=True)
 512       instances_ = paths
 513 
 514       instances = []
 515       for instance_ in instances_:
 516         instance = instance_
 517         for i in range(self.task_params.num_steps):
 518           instance.append(self.take_action([instance[-1]], [1])[0])
 519         instances.append(instance)
 520 
 521     elif self.task_params.move_type == 'shortest_path':
 522       _, _, _, _, paths = rng_target_dist_field(self.task_params.batch_size,
 523                                                 self.task.gtG, rng,
 524                                                 self.task_params.num_steps,
 525                                                 self.task_params.num_steps+1,
 526                                                 compute_path=True)
 527       instances = paths
 528 
 529     elif self.task_params.move_type == 'circle+forward':
 530       _, _, _, _, paths = rng_target_dist_field(self.task_params.batch_size,
 531                                                 self.task.gtG, rng, 0, 1,
 532                                                 compute_path=True)
 533       instances_ = paths
 534       instances = []
 535       for instance_ in instances_:
 536         instance = instance_
 537         for i in range(self.task_params.n_ori-1):
 538           instance.append(self.take_action([instance[-1]], [1])[0])
 539         while len(instance) <= self.task_params.num_steps:
 540           while self.take_action([instance[-1]], [3])[0] == instance[-1] and len(instance) <= self.task_params.num_steps:
 541             instance.append(self.take_action([instance[-1]], [2])[0])
 542           if len(instance) <= self.task_params.num_steps:
 543             instance.append(self.take_action([instance[-1]], [3])[0])
 544         instances.append(instance)
 545 
 546     # Do random perturbation if needed.
 547     perturbs = _gen_perturbs(rng, self.task_params.batch_size,
 548                              self.task_params.num_steps,
 549                              self.task_params.data_augment.lr_flip,
 550                              self.task_params.data_augment.delta_angle,
 551                              self.task_params.data_augment.delta_xy,
 552                              self.task_params.data_augment.structured)
 553     return instances, perturbs
 554 
 555   def worker(self, instances, perturbs):
 556     # Output the images and the free space.
 557 
 558     # Make the instances be all the same length.
 559     for i in range(len(instances)):
 560       for j in range(self.task_params.num_steps - len(instances[i]) + 1):
 561         instances[i].append(instances[i][-1])
 562       if perturbs[i].shape[0] < self.task_params.num_steps+1:
 563         p = np.zeros((self.task_params.num_steps+1, 4))
 564         p[:perturbs[i].shape[0], :] = perturbs[i]
 565         p[perturbs[i].shape[0]:, :] = perturbs[i][-1,:]
 566         perturbs[i] = p
 567 
 568     instances_ = []
 569     for instance in instances:
 570       instances_ = instances_ + instance
 571     perturbs_ = np.concatenate(perturbs, axis=0)
 572 
 573     instances_nodes = self.task.nodes[instances_,:]
 574     instances_nodes = [tuple(x) for x in instances_nodes]
 575 
 576     imgs_ = self.render_nodes(instances_nodes, perturbs_)
 577     imgs = []; next = 0;
 578     for instance in instances:
 579       img_i = []
 580       for _ in instance:
 581         img_i.append(imgs_[next])
 582         next = next+1
 583       imgs.append(img_i)
 584     imgs = np.array(imgs)
 585 
 586     # Render out the maps in the egocentric view for all nodes and not just the
 587     # last node.
 588     all_nodes = []
 589     for x in instances:
 590       all_nodes = all_nodes + x
 591     all_perturbs = np.concatenate(perturbs, axis=0)
 592     loc, x_axis, y_axis, theta = self.get_loc_axis(
 593         self.task.nodes[all_nodes, :]*1, delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
 594         perturb=all_perturbs)
 595     fss = None
 596     valids = None
 597     loc_on_map = None
 598     theta_on_map = None
 599     cum_fs = None
 600     cum_valid = None
 601     incremental_locs = None
 602     incremental_thetas = None
 603 
 604     if self.task_params.output_free_space:
 605       fss, valids = get_map_to_predict(loc, x_axis, y_axis,
 606                                        map=self.traversible*1.,
 607                                        map_size=self.task_params.map_size)
 608       fss = np.array(fss) > 0.5
 609       fss = np.reshape(fss, [self.task_params.batch_size,
 610                              self.task_params.num_steps+1,
 611                              self.task_params.map_size,
 612                              self.task_params.map_size])
 613       valids = np.reshape(np.array(valids), fss.shape)
 614 
 615     if self.task_params.output_transform_to_global_map:
 616       # Output the transform to the global map.
 617       loc_on_map = np.reshape(loc*1, [self.task_params.batch_size,
 618                                       self.task_params.num_steps+1, -1])
 619       # Converting to location wrt to first location so that warping happens
 620       # properly.
 621       theta_on_map = np.reshape(theta*1, [self.task_params.batch_size,
 622                                             self.task_params.num_steps+1, -1])
 623 
 624     if self.task_params.output_incremental_transform:
 625       # Output the transform to the global map.
 626       incremental_locs_ = np.reshape(loc*1, [self.task_params.batch_size,
 627                                              self.task_params.num_steps+1, -1])
 628       incremental_locs_[:,1:,:] -= incremental_locs_[:,:-1,:]
 629       t0 = -np.pi/2+np.reshape(theta*1, [self.task_params.batch_size,
 630                                         self.task_params.num_steps+1, -1])
 631       t = t0*1
 632       incremental_locs = incremental_locs_*1
 633       incremental_locs[:,:,0] = np.sum(incremental_locs_ * np.concatenate((np.cos(t), np.sin(t)), axis=-1), axis=-1)
 634       incremental_locs[:,:,1] = np.sum(incremental_locs_ * np.concatenate((np.cos(t+np.pi/2), np.sin(t+np.pi/2)), axis=-1), axis=-1)
 635       incremental_locs[:,0,:] = incremental_locs_[:,0,:]
 636       # print incremental_locs_[0,:,:], incremental_locs[0,:,:], t0[0,:,:]
 637 
 638       incremental_thetas = np.reshape(theta*1, [self.task_params.batch_size,
 639                                                 self.task_params.num_steps+1,
 640                                                 -1])
 641       incremental_thetas[:,1:,:] += -incremental_thetas[:,:-1,:]
 642 
 643     if self.task_params.output_canonical_map:
 644       loc_ = loc[0::(self.task_params.num_steps+1), :]
 645       x_axis = np.zeros_like(loc_); x_axis[:,1] = 1
 646       y_axis = np.zeros_like(loc_); y_axis[:,0] = -1
 647       cum_fs, cum_valid = get_map_to_predict(loc_, x_axis, y_axis,
 648                                              map=self.traversible*1.,
 649                                              map_size=self.task_params.map_size)
 650       cum_fs = np.array(cum_fs) > 0.5
 651       cum_fs = np.reshape(cum_fs, [self.task_params.batch_size, 1,
 652                                    self.task_params.map_size,
 653                                    self.task_params.map_size])
 654       cum_valid = np.reshape(np.array(cum_valid), cum_fs.shape)
 655 
 656 
 657     inputs = {'fs_maps': fss,
 658               'valid_maps': valids,
 659               'imgs': imgs,
 660               'loc_on_map': loc_on_map,
 661               'theta_on_map': theta_on_map,
 662               'cum_fs_maps': cum_fs,
 663               'cum_valid_maps': cum_valid,
 664               'incremental_thetas': incremental_thetas,
 665               'incremental_locs': incremental_locs}
 666     return inputs
 667 
 668   def pre(self, inputs):
 669     inputs['imgs'] = image_pre(inputs['imgs'], self.task_params.modalities)
 670     if inputs['loc_on_map'] is not None:
 671       inputs['loc_on_map'] = inputs['loc_on_map'] - inputs['loc_on_map'][:,[0],:]
 672     if inputs['theta_on_map'] is not None:
 673       inputs['theta_on_map'] = np.pi/2. - inputs['theta_on_map']
 674     return inputs

 676 def _nav_env_reset_helper(type, rng, nodes, batch_size, gtG, max_dist,
 677                           num_steps, num_goals, data_augment, **kwargs):
 678   """Generates and returns a new episode."""
 679   max_compute = max_dist + 4*num_steps
 680   if type == 'general':
 681     start_node_ids, end_node_ids, dist, pred_map, paths = \
 682         rng_target_dist_field(batch_size, gtG, rng, max_dist, max_compute,
 683                               nodes=nodes, compute_path=False)
 684     target_class = None
 685 
 686   elif type == 'room_to_room_many':
 687     goal_node_ids = []; dists = [];
 688     node_room_ids = kwargs['node_room_ids']
 689     # Sample the first one
 690     start_node_ids_, end_node_ids_, dist_, _, _ = rng_room_to_room(
 691         batch_size, gtG, rng, max_dist, max_compute,
 692         node_room_ids=node_room_ids, nodes=nodes)
 693     start_node_ids = start_node_ids_
 694     goal_node_ids.append(end_node_ids_)
 695     dists.append(dist_)
 696     for n in range(num_goals-1):
 697       start_node_ids_, end_node_ids_, dist_, _, _ = rng_next_goal(
 698           goal_node_ids[n], batch_size, gtG, rng, max_dist,
 699           max_compute, node_room_ids=node_room_ids, nodes=nodes,
 700           dists_from_start_node=dists[n])
 701       goal_node_ids.append(end_node_ids_)
 702       dists.append(dist_)
 703     target_class = None
 704 
 705   elif type == 'rng_rejection_sampling_many':
 706     num_goals = num_goals
 707     goal_node_ids = []; dists = [];
 708 
 709     n_ori = kwargs['n_ori']
 710     step_size = kwargs['step_size']
 711     min_dist = kwargs['min_dist']
 712     sampling_distribution = kwargs['sampling_distribution']
 713     target_distribution = kwargs['target_distribution']
 714     rejection_sampling_M = kwargs['rejection_sampling_M']
 715     distribution_bins = kwargs['distribution_bins']
 716 
 717     for n in range(num_goals):
 718       if n == 0: input_nodes = None
 719       else: input_nodes = goal_node_ids[n-1]
 720       start_node_ids_, end_node_ids_, dist_, _, _, _, _ = rng_next_goal_rejection_sampling(
 721               input_nodes, batch_size, gtG, rng, max_dist, min_dist,
 722               max_compute, sampling_distribution, target_distribution, nodes,
 723               n_ori, step_size, distribution_bins, rejection_sampling_M)
 724       if n == 0: start_node_ids = start_node_ids_
 725       goal_node_ids.append(end_node_ids_)
 726       dists.append(dist_)
 727     target_class = None
 728 
 729   elif type == 'room_to_room_back':
 730     num_goals = num_goals
 731     assert(num_goals == 2), 'num_goals must be 2.'
 732     goal_node_ids = []; dists = [];
 733     node_room_ids = kwargs['node_room_ids']
 734     # Sample the first one.
 735     start_node_ids_, end_node_ids_, dist_, _, _ = rng_room_to_room(
 736         batch_size, gtG, rng, max_dist, max_compute,
 737         node_room_ids=node_room_ids, nodes=nodes)
 738     start_node_ids = start_node_ids_
 739     goal_node_ids.append(end_node_ids_)
 740     dists.append(dist_)
 741 
 742     # Set second goal to be starting position, and compute distance to the start node.
 743     goal_node_ids.append(start_node_ids)
 744     dist = []
 745     for i in range(batch_size):
 746       dist_ = gt.topology.shortest_distance(
 747           gt.GraphView(gtG, reversed=True),
 748           source=gtG.vertex(start_node_ids[i]), target=None)
 749       dist_ = np.array(dist_.get_array())
 750       dist.append(dist_)
 751     dists.append(dist)
 752     target_class = None
 753 
 754   elif type[:14] == 'to_nearest_obj':
 755     # Generate an episode by sampling one of the target classes (with
 756     # probability proportional to the number of nodes in the world).
 757     # With the sampled class sample a node that is within some distance from
 758     # the sampled class.
 759     class_nodes   = kwargs['class_nodes']
 760     sampling      = kwargs['sampling']
 761     dist_to_class = kwargs['dist_to_class']
 762 
 763     assert(num_goals == 1), 'Only supports a single goal.'
 764     ind = rng.choice(class_nodes.shape[0], size=batch_size)
 765     target_class = class_nodes[ind,1]
 766     start_node_ids = []; dists = []; goal_node_ids = [];
 767 
 768     for t in target_class:
 769       if sampling == 'uniform':
 770         max_dist = max_dist
 771         cnts = np.bincount(dist_to_class[t], minlength=max_dist+1)*1.
 772         cnts[max_dist+1:] = 0
 773         p_each = 1./ cnts / (max_dist+1.)
 774         p_each[cnts == 0] = 0
 775         p = p_each[dist_to_class[t]]*1.; p = p/np.sum(p)
 776         start_node_id = rng.choice(p.shape[0], size=1, p=p)[0]
 777       else:
 778         logging.fatal('Sampling not one of uniform.')
 779       start_node_ids.append(start_node_id)
 780       dists.append(dist_to_class[t])
 781       # Dummy goal node, same as the start node, so that vis is better.
 782       goal_node_ids.append(start_node_id)
 783     dists = [dists]
 784     goal_node_ids = [goal_node_ids]
 785 
 786   return start_node_ids, goal_node_ids, dists, target_class

 856   def _preprocess_for_task(self, seed):
 857     """Sets up the task field for doing navigation on the grid world."""
 858     if self.task is None or self.task.seed != seed:
 859       rng = np.random.RandomState(seed)
 860       origin_loc = get_graph_origin_loc(rng, self.traversible)
 861       self.task = utils.Foo(seed=seed, origin_loc=origin_loc,
 862                             n_ori=self.task_params.n_ori)
 863       G = generate_graph(self.valid_fn_vec, self.task_params.step_size,
 864                          self.task.n_ori, (0, 0, 0))
 865       gtG, nodes, nodes_to_id = convert_to_graph_tool(G)
 866       self.task.gtG = gtG
 867       self.task.nodes = nodes
 868       self.task.delta_theta = 2.0*np.pi/(self.task.n_ori*1.)
 869       self.task.nodes_to_id = nodes_to_id
 870 
 871       logging.info('Building %s, #V=%d, #E=%d', self.building_name,
 872                    self.task.nodes.shape[0], self.task.gtG.num_edges())
 873       type = self.task_params.type
 874       if type == 'general':
 875         # Do nothing
 876         _ = None
 877 
 878       elif type == 'room_to_room_many' or type == 'room_to_room_back':
 879         if type == 'room_to_room_back':
 880           assert(self.task_params.num_goals == 2), 'num_goals must be 2.'
 881 
 882         self.room_dims = _filter_rooms(self.room_dims, self.task_params.room_regex)
 883         xyt = self.to_actual_xyt_vec(self.task.nodes)
 884         self.task.node_room_ids = _label_nodes_with_room_id(xyt, self.room_dims)
 885         self.task.reset_kwargs = {'node_room_ids': self.task.node_room_ids}
 886 
 887       elif type == 'rng_rejection_sampling_many':
 888         n_bins = 20
 889         rejection_sampling_M = self.task_params.rejection_sampling_M
 890         min_dist = self.task_params.min_dist
 891         bins = np.arange(n_bins+1)/(n_bins*1.)
 892         target_d = np.zeros(n_bins); target_d[...] = 1./n_bins;
 893 
 894         sampling_d = get_hardness_distribution(
 895             self.task.gtG, self.task_params.max_dist, self.task_params.min_dist,
 896             np.random.RandomState(0), 4000, bins, self.task.nodes,
 897             self.task_params.n_ori, self.task_params.step_size)
 898 
 899         self.task.reset_kwargs = {'distribution_bins': bins,
 900                                   'target_distribution': target_d,
 901                                   'sampling_distribution': sampling_d,
 902                                   'rejection_sampling_M': rejection_sampling_M,
 903                                   'n_bins': n_bins, 
 904                                   'n_ori': self.task_params.n_ori,
 905                                   'step_size': self.task_params.step_size,
 906                                   'min_dist': self.task_params.min_dist}
 907         self.task.n_bins = n_bins
 908         self.task.distribution_bins = bins
 909         self.task.target_distribution = target_d
 910         self.task.sampling_distribution = sampling_d
 911         self.task.rejection_sampling_M = rejection_sampling_M
 912 
 913         if self.logdir is not None:
 914           self._debug_save_hardness(seed)
 915 
 916       elif type[:14] == 'to_nearest_obj':
 917         self.room_dims = _filter_rooms(self.room_dims, self.task_params.room_regex)
 918         xyt = self.to_actual_xyt_vec(self.task.nodes)
 919 
 920         self.class_maps = _select_classes(self.class_maps,
 921                                           self.class_map_names,
 922                                           self.task_params.semantic_task.class_map_names)*1
 923         self.class_map_names = self.task_params.semantic_task.class_map_names
 924         nodes_xyt = self.to_actual_xyt_vec(np.array(self.task.nodes))
 925 
 926         tt = utils.Timer(); tt.tic();
 927         if self.task_params.type == 'to_nearest_obj_acc':
 928           self.task.class_maps_dilated, self.task.node_class_label = label_nodes_with_class_geodesic(
 929             nodes_xyt, self.class_maps,
 930             self.task_params.semantic_task.pix_distance+8, self.map.traversible,
 931             ff_cost=1., fo_cost=1., oo_cost=4., connectivity=8.)
 932 
 933         dists = []
 934         for i in range(len(self.class_map_names)):
 935           class_nodes_ = np.where(self.task.node_class_label[:,i])[0]
 936           dists.append(get_distance_node_list(gtG, source_nodes=class_nodes_, direction='to'))
 937         self.task.dist_to_class = dists
 938         a_, b_ = np.where(self.task.node_class_label)
 939         self.task.class_nodes = np.concatenate((a_[:,np.newaxis], b_[:,np.newaxis]), axis=1)
 940         
 941         if self.logdir is not None:
 942           self._debug_semantic_maps(seed)
 943         
 944         self.task.reset_kwargs = {'sampling': self.task_params.semantic_task.sampling,
 945                                   'class_nodes': self.task.class_nodes,
 946                                   'dist_to_class': self.task.dist_to_class}
 947 
 948       if self.logdir is not None:
 949         self._debug_save_map_nodes(seed)
 950 
 951   def reset(self, rngs):
 952     rng = rngs[0]; rng_perturb = rngs[1];
 953     nodes = self.task.nodes
 954     tp = self.task_params
 955 
 956     start_node_ids, goal_node_ids, dists, target_class = \
 957         _nav_env_reset_helper(tp.type, rng, self.task.nodes, tp.batch_size,
 958                               self.task.gtG, tp.max_dist, tp.num_steps,
 959                               tp.num_goals, tp.data_augment,
 960                               **(self.task.reset_kwargs))
 961 
 962     start_nodes = [tuple(nodes[_,:]) for _ in start_node_ids]
 963     goal_nodes = [[tuple(nodes[_,:]) for _ in __] for __ in goal_node_ids]
 964     data_augment = tp.data_augment
 965     perturbs = _gen_perturbs(rng_perturb, tp.batch_size,
 966                              (tp.num_steps+1)*tp.num_goals,
 967                              data_augment.lr_flip, data_augment.delta_angle,
 968                              data_augment.delta_xy, data_augment.structured)
 969     perturbs = np.array(perturbs) # batch x steps x 4
 970     end_perturbs = perturbs[:,-(tp.num_goals):,:]*1 # fixed perturb for the goal.
 971     perturbs = perturbs[:,:-(tp.num_goals),:]*1
 972 
 973     history = -np.ones((tp.batch_size, tp.num_steps*tp.num_goals), dtype=np.int32)
 974     self.episode = utils.Foo(
 975         start_nodes=start_nodes, start_node_ids=start_node_ids,
 976         goal_nodes=goal_nodes, goal_node_ids=goal_node_ids, dist_to_goal=dists,
 977         perturbs=perturbs, goal_perturbs=end_perturbs, history=history,
 978         target_class=target_class, history_frames=[])
 979     return start_node_ids

 981   def take_action(self, current_node_ids, action, step_number):
 982     """In addition to returning the action, also returns the reward that the
 983     agent receives."""
 984     goal_number = step_number / self.task_params.num_steps
 985     new_node_ids = GridWorld.take_action(self, current_node_ids, action)
 986     rewards = []
 987     for i, n in enumerate(new_node_ids):
 988       reward = 0
 989       if n == self.episode.goal_node_ids[goal_number][i]:
 990         reward = self.task_params.reward_at_goal
 991       reward = reward - self.task_params.reward_time_penalty
 992       rewards.append(reward)
 993     return new_node_ids, rewards

 996   def get_optimal_action(self, current_node_ids, step_number):
 997     """Returns the optimal action from the current node."""
 998     goal_number = step_number / self.task_params.num_steps
 999     gtG = self.task.gtG
1000     a = np.zeros((len(current_node_ids), self.task_params.num_actions), dtype=np.int32)
1001     d_dict = self.episode.dist_to_goal[goal_number]
1002     for i, c in enumerate(current_node_ids):
1003       neigh = gtG.vertex(c).out_neighbours()
1004       neigh_edge = gtG.vertex(c).out_edges()
1005       ds = np.array([d_dict[i][int(x)] for x in neigh])
1006       ds_min = np.min(ds)
1007       for i_, e in enumerate(neigh_edge):
1008         if ds[i_] == ds_min:
1009           _ = gtG.ep['action'][e]
1010           a[i, _] = 1
1011     return a
1012 
1013   def get_targets(self, current_node_ids, step_number):
1014     """Returns the target actions from the current node."""
1015     action = self.get_optimal_action(current_node_ids, step_number)
1016     action = np.expand_dims(action, axis=1)
1017     return vars(utils.Foo(action=action))

1059   def get_common_data(self):
1060     goal_nodes = self.episode.goal_nodes
1061     start_nodes = self.episode.start_nodes
1062     perturbs = self.episode.perturbs
1063     goal_perturbs = self.episode.goal_perturbs
1064     target_class = self.episode.target_class
1065 
1066     goal_locs = []; rel_goal_locs = [];
1067     for i in range(len(goal_nodes)):
1068       end_nodes = goal_nodes[i]
1069       goal_loc, _, _, goal_theta = self.get_loc_axis(
1070           np.array(end_nodes), delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1071           perturb=goal_perturbs[:,i,:])
1072 
1073       # Compute the relative location to all goals from the starting location.
1074       loc, _, _, theta = self.get_loc_axis(np.array(start_nodes),
1075                                            delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1076                                            perturb=perturbs[:,0,:])
1077       r_goal, t_goal = _get_relative_goal_loc(goal_loc*1., loc, theta)
1078       rel_goal_loc = np.concatenate((r_goal*np.cos(t_goal), r_goal*np.sin(t_goal),
1079                                      np.cos(goal_theta-theta),
1080                                      np.sin(goal_theta-theta)), axis=1)
1081       rel_goal_locs.append(np.expand_dims(rel_goal_loc, axis=1))
1082       goal_locs.append(np.expand_dims(goal_loc, axis=1))
1083 
1084     map = self.traversible*1.
1085     maps = np.repeat(np.expand_dims(np.expand_dims(map, axis=0), axis=0),
1086                      self.task_params.batch_size, axis=0)*1
1087     if self.task_params.type[:14] == 'to_nearest_obj':
1088       for i in range(self.task_params.batch_size):
1089         maps[i,0,:,:] += 0.5*(self.task.class_maps_dilated[:,:,target_class[i]])
1090 
1091     rel_goal_locs = np.concatenate(rel_goal_locs, axis=1)
1092     goal_locs = np.concatenate(goal_locs, axis=1)
1093     maps = np.expand_dims(maps, axis=-1)
1094 
1095     if self.task_params.type[:14] == 'to_nearest_obj':
1096       rel_goal_locs = np.zeros((self.task_params.batch_size, 1,
1097                                 len(self.task_params.semantic_task.class_map_names)),
1098                                dtype=np.float32)
1099       goal_locs = np.zeros((self.task_params.batch_size, 1, 2),
1100                            dtype=np.float32)
1101       for i in range(self.task_params.batch_size):
1102           t = target_class[i]
1103           rel_goal_locs[i,0,t] = 1.
1104           goal_locs[i,0,0] = t
1105           goal_locs[i,0,1] = np.NaN
1106 
1107     return vars(utils.Foo(orig_maps=maps, goal_loc=goal_locs,
1108                           rel_goal_loc_at_start=rel_goal_locs))

1114   def get_features(self, current_node_ids, step_number):
1115     task_params = self.task_params
1116     goal_number = step_number / self.task_params.num_steps
1117     end_nodes = self.task.nodes[self.episode.goal_node_ids[goal_number],:]*1
1118     current_nodes = self.task.nodes[current_node_ids,:]*1
1119     end_perturbs = self.episode.goal_perturbs[:,goal_number,:][:,np.newaxis,:]
1120     perturbs = self.episode.perturbs
1121     target_class = self.episode.target_class
1122 
1123     # Append to history.
1124     self.episode.history[:,step_number] = np.array(current_node_ids)
1125 
1126     # Render out the images from current node.
1127     outs = {}
1128 
1129     if self.task_params.outputs.images:
1130       imgs_all = []
1131       imgs = self.render_nodes([tuple(x) for x in current_nodes],
1132                                perturb=perturbs[:,step_number,:])
1133       imgs_all.append(imgs)
1134       aux_delta_thetas = self.task_params.aux_delta_thetas
1135       for i in range(len(aux_delta_thetas)):
1136         imgs = self.render_nodes([tuple(x) for x in current_nodes],
1137                                  perturb=perturbs[:,step_number,:],
1138                                  aux_delta_theta=aux_delta_thetas[i])
1139         imgs_all.append(imgs)
1140       imgs_all = np.array(imgs_all) # A x B x H x W x C
1141       imgs_all = np.transpose(imgs_all, axes=[1,0,2,3,4])
1142       imgs_all = np.expand_dims(imgs_all, axis=1) # B x N x A x H x W x C
1143       if task_params.num_history_frames > 0:
1144         if step_number == 0:
1145           # Append the same frame 4 times
1146           for i in range(task_params.num_history_frames+1):
1147             self.episode.history_frames.insert(0, imgs_all*1.)
1148         self.episode.history_frames.insert(0, imgs_all)
1149         self.episode.history_frames.pop()
1150         imgs_all_with_history = np.concatenate(self.episode.history_frames, axis=2)
1151       else:
1152         imgs_all_with_history = imgs_all
1153       outs['imgs'] = imgs_all_with_history # B x N x A x H x W x C
1154 
1155     if self.task_params.outputs.node_ids:
1156       outs['node_ids'] = np.array(current_node_ids).reshape((-1,1,1))
1157       outs['perturbs'] = np.expand_dims(perturbs[:,step_number, :]*1., axis=1)
1158 
1159     if self.task_params.outputs.analytical_counts:
1160       assert(self.task_params.modalities == ['depth'])
1161       d = image_pre(outs['imgs']*1., self.task_params.modalities)
1162       cm = get_camera_matrix(self.task_params.img_width,
1163                              self.task_params.img_height,
1164                              self.task_params.img_fov)
1165       XYZ = get_point_cloud_from_z(100./d[...,0], cm)
1166       XYZ = make_geocentric(XYZ*100., self.robot.sensor_height,
1167                                       self.robot.camera_elevation_degree)
1168       for i in range(len(self.task_params.analytical_counts.map_sizes)):
1169         non_linearity = self.task_params.analytical_counts.non_linearity[i]
1170         count, isvalid = bin_points(XYZ*1.,
1171                                     map_size=self.task_params.analytical_counts.map_sizes[i],
1172                                     xy_resolution=self.task_params.analytical_counts.xy_resolution[i],
1173                                     z_bins=self.task_params.analytical_counts.z_bins[i])
1174         assert(count.shape[2] == 1), 'only works for n_views equal to 1.'
1175         count = count[:,:,0,:,:,:]
1176         isvalid = isvalid[:,:,0,:,:,:]
1177         if non_linearity == 'none':
1178           None
1179         elif non_linearity == 'min10':
1180           count = np.minimum(count, 10.)
1181         elif non_linearity == 'sqrt':
1182           count = np.sqrt(count)
1183         else:
1184           logging.fatal('Undefined non_linearity.')
1185         outs['analytical_counts_{:d}'.format(i)] = count
1186 
1187     # Compute the goal location in the cordinate frame of the robot.
1188     if self.task_params.outputs.rel_goal_loc:
1189       if self.task_params.type[:14] != 'to_nearest_obj':
1190         loc, _, _, theta = self.get_loc_axis(current_nodes,
1191                                              delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1192                                              perturb=perturbs[:,step_number,:])
1193         goal_loc, _, _, goal_theta = self.get_loc_axis(end_nodes,
1194                                                        delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1195                                                        perturb=end_perturbs[:,0,:])
1196         r_goal, t_goal = _get_relative_goal_loc(goal_loc, loc, theta)
1197 
1198         rel_goal_loc = np.concatenate((r_goal*np.cos(t_goal), r_goal*np.sin(t_goal),
1199                                        np.cos(goal_theta-theta),
1200                                        np.sin(goal_theta-theta)), axis=1)
1201         outs['rel_goal_loc'] = np.expand_dims(rel_goal_loc, axis=1)
1202       elif self.task_params.type[:14] == 'to_nearest_obj':
1203         rel_goal_loc = np.zeros((self.task_params.batch_size, 1,
1204                                  len(self.task_params.semantic_task.class_map_names)),
1205                                 dtype=np.float32)
1206         for i in range(self.task_params.batch_size):
1207           t = target_class[i]
1208           rel_goal_loc[i,0,t] = 1.
1209         outs['rel_goal_loc'] = rel_goal_loc
1210 
1211     # Location on map to plot the trajectory during validation.
1212     if self.task_params.outputs.loc_on_map:
1213       loc, x_axis, y_axis, theta = self.get_loc_axis(current_nodes,
1214                                                      delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1215                                                      perturb=perturbs[:,step_number,:])
1216       outs['loc_on_map'] = np.expand_dims(loc, axis=1)
1217 
1218     # Compute gt_dist to goal
1219     if self.task_params.outputs.gt_dist_to_goal:
1220       gt_dist_to_goal = np.zeros((len(current_node_ids), 1), dtype=np.float32)
1221       for i, n in enumerate(current_node_ids):
1222         gt_dist_to_goal[i,0] = self.episode.dist_to_goal[goal_number][i][n]
1223       outs['gt_dist_to_goal'] = np.expand_dims(gt_dist_to_goal, axis=1)
1224 
1225     # Free space in front of you, map and goal as images.
1226     if self.task_params.outputs.ego_maps:
1227       loc, x_axis, y_axis, theta = self.get_loc_axis(current_nodes,
1228                                                      delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1229                                                      perturb=perturbs[:,step_number,:])
1230       maps = generate_egocentric_maps(self.task.scaled_maps,
1231                                       self.task_params.map_scales,
1232                                       self.task_params.map_crop_sizes, loc,
1233                                       x_axis, y_axis, theta)
1234 
1235       for i in range(len(self.task_params.map_scales)):
1236         outs['ego_maps_{:d}'.format(i)] = \
1237             np.expand_dims(np.expand_dims(maps[i], axis=1), axis=-1)
1238 
1239     if self.task_params.outputs.readout_maps:
1240       loc, x_axis, y_axis, theta = self.get_loc_axis(current_nodes,
1241                                                      delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1242                                                      perturb=perturbs[:,step_number,:])
1243       maps = generate_egocentric_maps(self.task.readout_maps_scaled,
1244                                       self.task_params.readout_maps_scales,
1245                                       self.task_params.readout_maps_crop_sizes,
1246                                       loc, x_axis, y_axis, theta)
1247       for i in range(len(self.task_params.readout_maps_scales)):
1248         outs['readout_maps_{:d}'.format(i)] = \
1249             np.expand_dims(np.expand_dims(maps[i], axis=1), axis=-1)
1250 
1251     # Images for the goal.
1252     if self.task_params.outputs.ego_goal_imgs:
1253       if self.task_params.type[:14] != 'to_nearest_obj': 
1254         loc, x_axis, y_axis, theta = self.get_loc_axis(current_nodes,
1255                                                        delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1256                                                        perturb=perturbs[:,step_number,:])
1257         goal_loc, _, _, _ = self.get_loc_axis(end_nodes,
1258                                               delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1259                                               perturb=end_perturbs[:,0,:])
1260         rel_goal_orientation = np.mod(
1261             np.int32(current_nodes[:,2:] - end_nodes[:,2:]), self.task_params.n_ori)
1262         goal_dist, goal_theta = _get_relative_goal_loc(goal_loc, loc, theta)
1263         goals = generate_goal_images(self.task_params.map_scales,
1264                                      self.task_params.map_crop_sizes,
1265                                      self.task_params.n_ori, goal_dist,
1266                                      goal_theta, rel_goal_orientation)
1267         for i in range(len(self.task_params.map_scales)):
1268           outs['ego_goal_imgs_{:d}'.format(i)] = np.expand_dims(goals[i], axis=1)
1269 
1270       elif self.task_params.type[:14] == 'to_nearest_obj':
1271         for i in range(len(self.task_params.map_scales)):
1272           num_classes = len(self.task_params.semantic_task.class_map_names)
1273           outs['ego_goal_imgs_{:d}'.format(i)] = np.zeros((self.task_params.batch_size, 1,
1274                                                            self.task_params.map_crop_sizes[i],
1275                                                            self.task_params.map_crop_sizes[i],
1276                                                            self.task_params.goal_channels))
1277         for i in range(self.task_params.batch_size):
1278           t = target_class[i]
1279           for j in range(len(self.task_params.map_scales)):
1280             outs['ego_goal_imgs_{:d}'.format(j)][i,:,:,:,t] = 1.
1281 
1282     # Incremental locs and theta (for map warping), always in the original scale
1283     # of the map, the subequent steps in the tf code scale appropriately.
1284     # Scaling is done by just multiplying incremental_locs appropriately.
1285     if self.task_params.outputs.egomotion:
1286       if step_number == 0:
1287         # Zero Ego Motion
1288         incremental_locs = np.zeros((self.task_params.batch_size, 1, 2), dtype=np.float32)
1289         incremental_thetas = np.zeros((self.task_params.batch_size, 1, 1), dtype=np.float32)
1290       else:
1291         previous_nodes = self.task.nodes[self.episode.history[:,step_number-1], :]*1
1292         loc, _, _, theta = self.get_loc_axis(current_nodes,
1293                                              delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1294                                              perturb=perturbs[:,step_number,:])
1295         previous_loc, _, _, previous_theta = self.get_loc_axis(
1296             previous_nodes, delta_theta=self.task.delta_theta,
1297             perturb=perturbs[:,step_number-1,:])
1298 
1299         incremental_locs_ = np.reshape(loc-previous_loc, [self.task_params.batch_size, 1, -1])
1300 
1301         t = -np.pi/2+np.reshape(theta*1, [self.task_params.batch_size, 1, -1])
1302         incremental_locs = incremental_locs_*1
1303         incremental_locs[:,:,0] = np.sum(incremental_locs_ *
1304                                          np.concatenate((np.cos(t), np.sin(t)),
1305                                                         axis=-1), axis=-1)
1306         incremental_locs[:,:,1] = np.sum(incremental_locs_ *
1307                                          np.concatenate((np.cos(t+np.pi/2),
1308                                                          np.sin(t+np.pi/2)),
1309                                                         axis=-1), axis=-1)
1310         incremental_thetas = np.reshape(theta-previous_theta,
1311                                         [self.task_params.batch_size, 1, -1])
1312       outs['incremental_locs'] = incremental_locs
1313       outs['incremental_thetas'] = incremental_thetas
1314 
1315     if self.task_params.outputs.visit_count:
1316       # Output the visit count for this state, how many times has the current
1317       # state been visited, and how far in the history was the last visit
1318       # (except this one)
1319       visit_count = np.zeros((self.task_params.batch_size, 1), dtype=np.int32)
1320       last_visit = -np.ones((self.task_params.batch_size, 1), dtype=np.int32)
1321       if step_number >= 1:
1322         h = self.episode.history[:,:(step_number)]
1323         visit_count[:,0] = np.sum(h == np.array(current_node_ids).reshape([-1,1]),
1324                                   axis=1)
1325         last_visit[:,0] = np.argmax(h[:,::-1] == np.array(current_node_ids).reshape([-1,1]),
1326                                     axis=1) + 1
1327         last_visit[visit_count == 0] = -1 # -1 if not visited.
1328       outs['visit_count'] = np.expand_dims(visit_count, axis=1)
1329       outs['last_visit'] = np.expand_dims(last_visit, axis=1)
1330     return outs

1358       for i in range(len(self.task_params.analytical_counts.map_sizes)):
1359         f.append('analytical_counts_{:d}'.format(i))
1360     if self.task_params.outputs.node_ids:
1361       f.append('node_ids')
1362       f.append('perturbs')
1363     return f
1364 
1365   def pre_features(self, inputs):
1366     if self.task_params.outputs.images:
1367       inputs['imgs'] = image_pre(inputs['imgs'], self.task_params.modalities)
1368     return inputs

1370 class BuildingMultiplexer():
1371   def __init__(self, args, task_number):
1372     params = vars(args)
1373     for k in params.keys():
1374       setattr(self, k, params[k])
1375     self.task_number = task_number
1376     self._pick_data(task_number)
1377     logging.info('Env Class: %s.', self.env_class)
1378     if self.task_params.task == 'planning':
1379       self._setup_planner()
1380     elif self.task_params.task == 'mapping':
1381       self._setup_mapper()
1382     elif self.task_params.task == 'map+plan':
1383       self._setup_mapper()
1384     else:
1385       logging.error('Undefined task: %s'.format(self.task_params.task))
1386 
1387   def _pick_data(self, task_number):
1388     logging.error('Input Building Names: %s', self.building_names)
1389     self.flip = [np.mod(task_number / len(self.building_names), 2) == 1]
1390     id = np.mod(task_number, len(self.building_names))
1391     self.building_names = [self.building_names[id]]
1392     self.task_params.building_seed = task_number
1393     logging.error('BuildingMultiplexer: Picked Building Name: %s', self.building_names)
1394     self.building_names = self.building_names[0].split('+')
1395     self.flip = [self.flip[0] for _ in self.building_names]
1396     logging.error('BuildingMultiplexer: Picked Building Name: %s', self.building_names)
1397     logging.error('BuildingMultiplexer: Flipping Buildings: %s', self.flip)
1398     logging.error('BuildingMultiplexer: Set building_seed: %d', self.task_params.building_seed)
1399     self.num_buildings = len(self.building_names)
1400     logging.error('BuildingMultiplexer: Num buildings: %d', self.num_buildings)
1401 
1402   def _setup_planner(self):
1403     # Load building env class.
1404     self.buildings = []
1405     for i, building_name in enumerate(self.building_names):
1406       b = self.env_class(robot=self.robot, env=self.env,
1407                          task_params=self.task_params,
1408                          building_name=building_name, flip=self.flip[i],
1409                          logdir=self.logdir, building_loader=self.dataset)
1410       self.buildings.append(b)
1411 
1412   def _setup_mapper(self):
1413     # Set up the renderer.
1414     cp = self.camera_param
1415     rgb_shader, d_shader = sru.get_shaders(cp.modalities)
1416     r_obj = SwiftshaderRenderer()
1417     r_obj.init_display(width=cp.width, height=cp.height, fov=cp.fov,
1418                        z_near=cp.z_near, z_far=cp.z_far, rgb_shader=rgb_shader,
1419                        d_shader=d_shader)
1420     self.r_obj = r_obj
1421     r_obj.clear_scene()
1422 
1423     # Load building env class.
1424     self.buildings = []
1425     wt = []
1426     for i, building_name in enumerate(self.building_names):
1427       b = self.env_class(robot=self.robot, env=self.env,
1428                          task_params=self.task_params,
1429                          building_name=building_name, flip=self.flip[i],
1430                          logdir=self.logdir, building_loader=self.dataset,
1431                          r_obj=r_obj)
1432       wt.append(b.get_weight())
1433       b.load_building_into_scene()
1434       b.set_building_visibility(False)
1435       self.buildings.append(b)
1436     wt = np.array(wt).astype(np.float32)
1437     wt = wt / np.sum(wt+0.0001)
1438     self.building_sampling_weights = wt
1439 
1440   def sample_building(self, rng):
1441     if self.num_buildings == 1:
1442       building_id = rng.choice(range(len(self.building_names)))
1443     else:
1444       building_id = rng.choice(self.num_buildings,
1445                                p=self.building_sampling_weights)
1446     b = self.buildings[building_id]
1447     instances = b._gen_rng(rng)
1448     self._building_id = building_id
1449     return self.buildings[building_id], instances
1450 
1451   def sample_env(self, rngs):
1452     rng = rngs[0];
1453     if self.num_buildings == 1:
1454       building_id = rng.choice(range(len(self.building_names)))
1455     else:
1456       building_id = rng.choice(self.num_buildings,
1457                                p=self.building_sampling_weights)
1458     return self.buildings[building_id]
1459 
1460   def pre(self, inputs):
1461     return self.buildings[self._building_id].pre(inputs)
1462   
1463   def __del__(self):
1464     self.r_obj.clear_scene()
1465     logging.error('Clearing scene.')
